            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-Hd1e108">Rubrica 8</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De turpi et mala vita spernenda et mortis acceptabilitate</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="43"/>
      ¶ De turpi et mala vita spernenda et mortis
      <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>acceptabilitatate. ¶ Rubrica. 8. <!--328.xml-->
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-d1e123">
               <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
               <lb ed="#V" n="45"/> <ref>PSalmista. 33 pslamus</ref>
      <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-Qd1e131">Mors
        <lb ed="#V" n="47"/>peccatorum pessima.</quote> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-d1e137">
               <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>¶ <ref>Iesus filius sirach: in ecclesiast.
        <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>c. 30.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-Qd1e141">Melius est mors quam vita amara.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-d1e148"> 
        / <ref>40
        <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-Qd1e150">Melius est mori quam idigere.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-d1e156"> 
        / <ref>41.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-Qd1e158">O mors
        <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>bonum est iudicium tuum homini indigenti: et qui
        <lb ed="#V" n="52"/>minoratur viribus defecto etate.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-d1e166">
               <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>¶ <ref>Tullius phylippicorum vel. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-Qd1e170">Ad decus: et li
        <lb ed="#V" n="54" break="no"/>bertatem nati sumus: aut hoc teneamus: aut
        <lb ed="#V" n="55"/>cum dignitate moriamur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-d1e178">
               <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>¶ <ref>Quintilianus declam. declam. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-Qd1e182">Inter lu
        <lb ed="#V" n="57" break="no"/>ctus et despationes feda viuacitate duramus</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-d1e188">
               <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>¶ <ref>Seneca tragediarum in hercule etheo. c. 2.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="59"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-Qd1e192">Mortis hebet vices: Lente cum trahitur vita ge
        <lb ed="#V" n="60" break="no"/>mitibus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-d1e200"> 
        / <ref>Idem epistolarum ad lucillum vel. 9 e. i.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="61"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-Qd1e202">Non viuere bonum est: sed bene viuere. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-d1e209">
               <lb ed="#V" n="62"/>¶ <ref>Boetius de consolatione l. i. c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-Qd1e213">Mors ho
        <lb ed="#V" n="63" break="no"/>minum felix que se nec dulcibus annis
        <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>Inserit: et mestis sepe vocata venit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-d1e221">
               <lb ed="#V" n="65"/>¶ <ref>Isydorus solliloquiorum. l. i. c. i.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="66"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-e11025-Qd1e225">Mors malorum omnium finem imponit.
        <lb ed="#V" n="67"/>Mors calamitatis terminum prebet.
        <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>Omnem calamitatem mors adimit.
        <lb ed="#V" n="69"/>Melius est bene mori quam male viuere.
        <lb ed="#V" n="70"/>Melius est non esse quam infeliciter esse.</quote>
            </p>
